  "text": "Envoy implements gRPC health check protocol compliance through a dedicated gRPC health checker module. The implementation is centered in source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.cc and health_checker_impl.h, which define the GrpcHealthCheckerFactory and GrpcHealthCheckerImpl classes. The factory creates the health checker, while GrpcHealthCheckerImpl extends HealthCheckerImplBase (source/extensions/health_checkers/common/health_checker_base_impl.h/cc) to provide gRPC-specific health checking functionality.\n\nThe gRPC health check protocol implementation follows this flow:\n\n1. **Service Discovery & Configuration**: GrpcHealthCheckerFactory::createCustomHealthChecker creates instances configured via envoy.config.core.v3.HealthCheck.GrpcHealthCheck message (api/envoy/config/core/v3/health_check.proto), which specifies service_name, authority header, and initial_metadata for health check requests.\n\n2. **Health Check Request Creation**: GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession::onInterval() initiates periodic health checks. It creates a grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckRequest message and uses Grpc::Common::prepareHeaders() to prepare HTTP/2 headers targeting the grpc.health.v1.Health.Check RPC method. The service name (if configured) is serialized into the request message.\n\n3. **Response Parsing & Status Validation**: The session's decodeHeaders(), decodeData(), and decodeTrailers() methods handle HTTP/2 response streaming:\n   - decodeHeaders() validates that the response is a valid gRPC response using Common::isGrpcResponseHeaders() (source/common/grpc/common.cc)\n   - decodeData() parses gRPC frames and deserializes the grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse message\n   - decodeTrailers() extracts the gRPC status code from trailers using Common::getGrpcStatus()\n\n4. **Status Mapping**: The implementation handles HTTP status to gRPC status mapping through Utility::httpToGrpcStatus() (source/common/grpc/status.cc), which maps HTTP response codes (400, 401, 403, 404, 429, 502-504) to standard gRPC status codes (Internal, Unauthenticated, PermissionDenied, Unimplemented, Unavailable) per https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/doc/http-grpc-status-mapping.md.\n\n5. **Health Check Result Determination**: GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession::isHealthCheckSucceeded() determines health status by checking:\n   - The gRPC status code equals OK\n   - The HealthCheckResponse.status field equals grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse::SERVING\n\n6. **Service Status Logging**: GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession::logHealthCheckStatus() maps response status values (SERVING, NOT_SERVING, UNKNOWN, SERVICE_UNKNOWN) to human-readable strings for logging.\n\nThe protocol implementation strictly follows the gRPC health checking specification defined in src/proto/grpc/health/v1/health.proto (grpc/grpc repository), which defines the Health service with Check and Watch RPCs and the HealthCheckRequest and HealthCheckResponse message structures."
